President Obama met with faith leaders in the Oval Office to discuss the need for immigration reform. The faith leaders shared stories about how the broken immigration system affects families in their communities. The President expressed concern about the pain caused by the separation of families and emphasized that legislative reform is the only permanent solution. Both the President and the religious leaders expressed their commitment to immigration reform and pledged to continue urging Congress to take action. The President thanked the faith leaders for their leadership on this issue.